Holder Communications Corp said itagreed to buy five privately held companies with combined 1987revenues expected to be about 25 mln dlrs.    Holder plans to issue 32 mln common shares to buy theNashville-based companies, all of which are owned by JackNorman and Joe Shaw, their families and employees.    The companies include radio stations WKXC-AM and WWKZ-FM,which operate in the New Albany/Tupelo, Miss., market, andGeneral Masonry Inc, a contractor in the Southeast.    The acquisitions are subject to approval by Holdershareholders and the Federal Communications Commission. Reuter&#3;